<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=105011094829784></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105011094829784><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=105011094829784>RE: Newbie with help!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=105011094829784#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=147821><span id=Sage>Aggrok</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>224 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 11th 10:06 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;I honestly have never found it a problem to be an Ogre shaman. I can get all my tradeskill supplies in Neriak except alchemy herbs, which I can get in either Oggok or Shadow Haven. General consensus among shaman is that Trolls and Ogres make the best shaman, it depends whether or not you plan on playing your shaman like a hybrid. If you like to get your hands dirty and be able to melee mobs to 50+, Ogres are the way to go with non stun from the front. Ogres also have like 606 starting points to begin with, which is like 25-30 points more than most other races. Furthermore we start out with the most STR and STA , the latter of which determines Hp's. Ogre have good vision too but we have a 15% XP penalty. <br><br>Trolls have good STR and STA too, but less than Ogres and less WIS to start as well, but that regen is sweet. They have the same vision as Ogres ( infravision ) but have a 20% penalty. Stay away from mobs that use fire nukes as your starting FR is like 5 or get some FR gear as soon as you can. <br><br>Iksar have same regen as trolls, infravision, alot more quests they can do and a very good starting city, but also have a 20% XP penalty. The biggest downside for Iksar besides faction is they cant use any of the Jaundiced Bone armor, including that magic bracer. They do have naturally higher AC but getting an Iksar equipped well can be a bit more problematic than any other race.<br><br>Barbs, Vah Shir, and Frogs I think have a 5% XP penalty and are all welcome in the good cities, but have no real special skills or race attributes. <br><br>No matter what race shaman you pick you get 30 starting points, put 25 into WISdom and the other 5 into STA or maybe AGI. Dont boost STR, DEX, CHA or INT as these stats arent important to shaman. Cha is highlighted as a major skill for shaman, but we only have the level 29 and 34 charm spells that CHA affects and they are never used as our pets are better. The only other use for CHA is buying and selling stuff to vendors.<br><br>If I had to remake my shaman it would be a toss up between and Ogre or an Innoruuk worshipping troll as they can get a snare necklace from the cleric guild quests in Neriak. Keep in mind in the upper end of the game an ogre can get a regen BP like iksar BP or Fungi tunic, but trolls cant get an item that makes them non-stunnable from the front. Either way you go troll and ogre shaman are very rare, accounting for only maybe 10% of shaman level 50+, atleast on Luclin server ( most are barbs ).<br><br>59 Ogre Luminary on Luclin server--Chaotic Winds--Venerable Aggrok<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
